%% Offline Sync -- local-first write path and sync queue behavior
%% Referenced in: docs/mobile.md, docs/scalability.md (Failure Recovery)
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Written: Doctor writes/edits note
    Written --> LocalDrift: Immediate write to Drift (SQLite)
    LocalDrift --> AutosaveDebounce: 2s autosave debounce
    AutosaveDebounce --> Saved: state re-read after async save completes
    Saved --> SyncDebounce: 3s sync debounce
    SyncDebounce --> Online: connectivity check
    Online --> Syncing: enqueue in sync_queue_service
    Syncing --> Synced: backend accepts
    Syncing --> Failed: network error
    Failed --> Syncing: retry (RetryInterceptor, exponential backoff + jitter)

    note right of Syncing
        Known gap: _pendingNotes is an
        in-memory List<DoctorNote>.
        An OS-killed app while offline
        loses queue state (notes remain
        safe in Drift, but the app forgets
        they still need to sync).
        Planned fix: persist queue as a
        Drift table with a status enum.
    end note

    Online --> Offline: no connectivity
    Offline --> Online: connectivity restored
